Subject:    Help me save a subdomain
From:       <a href="?a=95837818200001&r=1&w=2">mccrave () ssd ! Kodak ! Com (Donna L McCrave (253-7148))</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=199011">1990-11-12 11:21:19</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837798827105&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837798827105&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I have a configuration question that I've been wrestling
with for a couple of months and need the omnipotence of this
mailing list to solve it.

There is a subdomain here which is implementing a very strange
set up that I believe is incorrect, but lack the expertise to
inform the proper administrators just exactly why it won't work.

Here is the setup:

There is a subdomain, call it ABC.Kodak.COM.   There is a drive
afoot to have several subdomains live under ABC, but to use
CNAMES to hide this fact from the user community at large (both
inside and outside of ABC).  So, for example, the mail hub
is known as mailhub.ABC.Kodak.COM.  Under the new configuration,
this will merely be a CNAME to the real name, 
mailhub.PLANT1.ABC.Kodak.COM.  The A and MX records will be
defined under the domain PLANT1.ABC.Kodak.COM.

So there will be hundreds of CNAMES crossing subdomain boundaries!
Intuitively, this seems really broken to me as it turns the
tree structure into a privet hedge.

Can anyone verify that this is a broken configuration, and if
so, tell me exactly why?  They haven't believed me so far.....


Donna McCrave
mccrave@Kodak.COM

